    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Analyze NPS responses with MySQL and Jira at scale\n\n**Pattern:** Survey & Feedback · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAnalyze NPS responses with MySQL and Jira at scale. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual auto-reply is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Stamp & Shape Ticket → Payload Valid? → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Microsoft Teams → Open Jira Ticket → Collect All Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to survey & feedback without manual effort\n- Anyone automating auto-reply in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Jira credentials; Microsoft OAuth2; MySQL connection; OpenRouter API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "843de1e9-3342-2c25-5ebd-607e171713f4",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "d5f40204-22dc-ba1b-4e58-2baec6d73cfe",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
